d archival photographs and images, Thompson brings together debates in German, African American, and jazz studies, and charts a new path for addressing antiblack racism in cultural criticism and theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aBlacksxRace identityzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aBlacks-Race identity-Germany-History-20th century. 0aJazzzGermanyy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aJazz-Germany-20th century-History and criticism. 0aPhilosophy, Germany20th century. 0aPhilosophy, German-20th century. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aCultural Studies : German Culture. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Music. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2018z978311149142440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438469881423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438469881/original  a978-3-11-149142-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles